By several accounts, Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein was expected to leave the Department of Justice shortly after William Barr was confirmed as Attorney General.
Now a month later Rosenstein is still there with no plans to leave (yet).
Rosenstein had planned to step down in mid-March but hasn't yet given his two weeks notice.
— Kevin Corke (@kevincorke) March 19, 2019Speculation has long been that Rosenstein would want to stay on until the Mueller investigation was completed.
